|WKBSyntax: |YKBset screenreader <on/off>|WKB
|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOScreenreader mode reshapes Darkwind's output for players who use a
screenreader. While it is on:

  - Colors, screen decoration, and decorative divider lines are
    stripped, and boxed headings are simplified to plain text.
  - Lists and tables, such as room contents and your settings, are
    printed as short numbered lines instead of drawn boxes.
  - Combat is summarized into a sentence or two each round instead of
    a stream of blow-by-blow lines.
  - Channel chatter is rephrased as plain speech, for example:
    Aeon says on Gossip, "Hello."
  - Ambient background noise is suppressed.

Enabling: you are asked at character creation whether you use a
screenreader. Answering yes turns the mode on and applies friendly
defaults -- plain terminal, monitor off, popups off, and quieter
channel settings. Review them with |YKBset list|YKO. You can also toggle
the mode at any time:

  |YKBset screenreader on|YKO
  |YKBset screenreader off|YKO

Help: while the mode is on, the |YKBhelp|YKO command reads a
screenreader-specific version of a topic when one exists and falls
back to the regular topic otherwise. Plain |YKBhelp|YKO opens a start
page written for screenreader users, and topics are shown through the
pager rather than in pop-up windows.|XX0

